# AEM Cloud Service - Frontend Development Guidelines

## Project Context
This is an AEM Cloud Service project using the standard Maven archetype structure.
- **Build tool**: Webpack (webpack.common.js, webpack.dev.js, webpack.prod.js)
- **CSS preprocessor**: SASS/SCSS compiled via webpack
- **JS transpiler**: Babel with TypeScript support
- **Clientlib generator**: aem-clientlib-generator (clientlib.config.js)
- **PostCSS**: Autoprefixer via postcss.config.js
- **Local AEM**: http://localhost:4502 (author), http://localhost:4503 (publish)

## Project Structure
```
ui.apps/          → Component HTL, dialog XML, clientlib definitions
ui.frontend/      → SASS, JS source (webpack compiles to ui.apps/clientlibs)
ui.content/       → Content pages, templates, policies
ui.config/        → OSGi configurations
dispatcher/       → Dispatcher rules, filters, rewrites
```

## HTL (Sightly) Rules
- Always use `data-sly-use` for Sling Model or Use-API references
- Use `data-sly-test` for conditionals, never inline JS logic
- Use `data-sly-list` or `data-sly-repeat` for iterations
- Use `data-sly-template` and `data-sly-call` for reusable markup fragments
- Use `data-sly-resource` to include child components
- Always escape output with `${properties.title @ context='html'}` or appropriate context
- Never use `data-sly-unwrap` unless absolutely necessary
- Use `data-sly-attribute` for dynamic HTML attributes
- Keep HTL files clean — no business logic, only presentation

## Component Dialog XML Rules
- Use Coral UI 3 / Granite UI widgets
- Dialog root: `jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"` with `sling:resourceType="cq/gui/components/authoring/dialog"`
- Tab structure: use `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/fixedcolumns` or `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/tabs`
- Common field types:
  - Text: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/textfield`
  - Textarea: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/textarea`
  - Path picker: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/pathfield`
  - Image: `cq/gui/components/authoring/dialog/fileupload`
  - Checkbox: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/checkbox`
  - Select/Dropdown: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/select`
  - Multifield: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/multifield`
  - RTE: `cq/gui/components/authoring/dialog/richtext`
  - Color picker: `granite/ui/components/coral/foundation/form/colorfield`
- Always set `name` attribute with `./` prefix (e.g., `name="./title"`)
- Always set `fieldLabel` for accessibility
- Use `required="{Boolean}true"` for mandatory fields

## SASS/CSS Rules
- BEM naming convention: `.block__element--modifier`
- Mobile-first responsive approach
- Use CSS custom properties for design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- Max nesting depth: 3 levels
- No `!important` unless overriding AEM editor styles
- Component SASS files in `ui.frontend/src/components/`
- Global styles in `ui.frontend/src/site/`
- Import order: variables → mixins → base → components → utilities
- Use AEM responsive grid classes: `aem-Grid`, `aem-GridColumn`
- Breakpoints: mobile (< 768px), tablet (768px - 1024px), desktop (> 1024px)

## JavaScript Rules
- ES6 modules, transpiled by Babel
- Component JS in `ui.frontend/src/components/`
- Site-level JS in `ui.frontend/src/site/`
- No global scope pollution — wrap in IIFE or use ES6 modules
- Use `DOMContentLoaded` or `MutationObserver` for initialization
- Event delegation pattern (components get destroyed/recreated in AEM editor)
- No `document.write`, no synchronous XHR, no inline event handlers
- Lazy load below-fold component JS
- JSDoc comments on all exported functions
- Handle author-mode vs publish-mode differences gracefully

## Clientlib Rules
- Categories follow pattern: `<project>.site`, `<project>.vendor`, `<project>.dependencies`
- clientlib.config.js maps webpack output → AEM clientlib structure
- Never add render-blocking JS — use `async` or `defer` loading categories
- Keep vendor libs in separate clientlib category
- CSS loads in `<head>`, JS loads before `</body>`

## Accessibility
- All images must have `alt` attributes (use `data-sly-attribute.alt`)
- Form fields must have associated labels
- Use semantic HTML elements (nav, main, article, section, aside, footer)
- Color contrast ratio minimum 4.5:1 (AA)
- Keyboard navigable — visible focus states on all interactive elements
- ARIA attributes only when native semantics are insufficient

## Performance
- Target Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, TBT < 200ms
- No render-blocking resources
- Optimize images: use `<picture>` with srcset for responsive images
- Lazy load images below the fold with `loading="lazy"`
- Minimize clientlib bundle size — tree-shake unused code
- Use appropriate dispatcher cache headers

## Code Generation Preferences
- When generating a component, always create ALL files: HTL, dialog XML, SASS, JS
- Follow existing project patterns — check similar components before generating new ones
- Include inline comments explaining AEM-specific patterns
- Generate mobile-first responsive styles
- Include empty state / placeholder handling for author mode
